    "Background": {
      "text": "Accumulation of fluid around the testis\nMost common cause of painless scrotal swelling in children\nSecondary to persistent processus vaginalis\nMost are right sided\nMost resorb by 18-24 months of age\nAcute symptomatic hydroceles are not benign, require workup",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
